abstract: The furor that led to the Secret Service chief’s resignation resonated among blacks who suspect that security lapses may be deliberate.
snippet: The furor that led to the Secret Service chief’s resignation resonated among blacks who suspect that security lapses may be deliberate.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Elijah E. Cummings of Maryland was at the grocery store the other day when he ran into an elderly black woman who expressed growing concern about President Obama’s safety. Why, she asked, wasn’t he being better protected by his Secret Service agents?

lead_paragraph: 10 P.M. (ABC) HOW TO GET AWAY WITH MURDER This latest entry from ShondaLand — Shonda Rhimes’s production company — to join ABC’s Thursday night lineup stars the Oscar-nominated Viola Davis as Annalise Keating, an intimidating law professor at a Philadelphia college, the likes of whom hasn’t been seen since Prof. Charles Kingsfield (John Houseman) caused the knees of aspiring legal eagles to knock in “The Paper Chase.” Aja Naomi King, Alfred Enoch, Jack Falahee, Karla Souza and Matt McGorry play Keating’s prized pupils, first seen toting a dead body in a rug around campus. Peter Nowalk created this series, which shuttles between the past and present as, thread by thread, it unravels who did what and why. In “Grey’s Anatomy,” leading in at 8, Meredith (Ellen Pompeo) seeks to regain control of her life as a new doctor (Kelly McCreary) comes on board and Derek (Patrick Dempsey) pushes to move to Washington. And in “Scandal,” at 9, Fitz (Tony Goldwyn) begins his second term in the White House determined to make a positive impact on the country; Mellie (Bellamy Young) copes with the loss of her son; and everybody tries to figure out where Olivia (Kerry Washington) and Jake (Scott Foley) have run off to.

abstract: A new take on Shakespeare’s “Antony and Cleopatra” at the McCarter Theater Center in Princeton focuses on the raging romance rather than the battles.
snippet: A new take on Shakespeare’s “Antony and Cleopatra” at the McCarter Theater Center in Princeton focuses on the raging romance rather than the battles.
lead_paragraph: Passions, power, allegiances — everything shifts during Shakespeare’s “Antony and Cleopatra.” In a staging directed by Emily Mann at the McCarter Theater Center in Princeton, the only constant is the production itself — it’s always beautifully bold.

abstract: Omar Gonzalez, the intruder, was arrested in July in Virginia after the state police there found several loaded semiautomatic weapons in his car after a high-speed chase on Interstate 81.
snippet: Omar Gonzalez, the intruder, was arrested in July in Virginia after the state police there found several loaded semiautomatic weapons in his car after a high-speed chase on Interstate 81.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secret Service officers stopped Omar Jose Gonzalez last month as he carried a hatchet in front of the White House, but let him go even though he had been arrested this summer in Virginia with a mini-arsenal of semiautomatic weapons, a sniper rifle and a map clearly marking the White House’s location.
